  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Factor: f(x) = x(x\u00b2 \u2212 16) = x(x + 4)(x \u2212 4) and g(x) = (x + 1)(x \u2212 4). For x &gt; 4 (so x \u2212 4 \u2260 0), f(x)/g(x) = x(x + 4)(x \u2212 4) / [(x + 1)(x \u2212 4)] = x(x + 4)/(x + 1).</p><p>The other choices result from incorrect factoring or cancellation.</p>",
